---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — NTE Codex" description="Why this site exists and how the AI-driven content pipeline works.">
  <h1>About NTE Codex</h1>
  <div class="prose-game max-w-prose">
    <p>
      NTE Codex is an unofficial fan database for <strong>Neverness to Everness</strong>,
      a 2026 urban-supernatural gacha RPG by Hotta Studio (published by Perfect World).
      We are not affiliated with the developer or publisher.
    </p>

    <h2>How content is made</h2>
    <p>
      Every article on this site goes through a multi-stage AI pipeline:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>KeywordSelector</strong> picks tomorrow's article from a curated keyword pool, balancing search demand against content-type diversity.</li>
      <li><strong>OutlineAgent</strong> drafts the structure using Google Search grounding so the article maps to the latest community knowledge.</li>
      <li><strong>WritingAgent</strong> produces the body in Markdown with required tables and source citations.</li>
      <li><strong>QAAgent</strong> independently scores the result on six dimensions including <em>factual_accuracy</em>: any unverifiable proper noun is flagged and the article rewrites.</li>
      <li><strong>PublishAgent</strong> writes the file to the site repo with frontmatter, sources, and a quality score.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We publish QA scores transparently on every article so readers can see exactly
      how confident the system is in each piece of content.
    </p>

    <h2>What we're <em>not</em></h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Not the official wiki — for the canonical word, visit Hotta Studio's channels.</li>
      <li>Not a replacement for community guides on Reddit or Discord — we link to those whenever they're the best source.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Found an error? See the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
